article.headline: Oral Roberts 78, Centenary 65
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Dominique Morrison scored 18 points to lead Oral Roberts past Centenary 78-65 on Saturday night, stretching the Gents? losing streak to 26 -- longest in NCAA Division I basketball. Damen Bell-Holter and Warren Niles added 13 points each for the Golden Eagles (9-12, 6-3 Summit League), who have won four in a row. Logan Lowery and Travis Sims scored 12 points each to lead the Gents (0-21, 0-9), who are in their final Division I season before moving to Division III. Oral Roberts led 41-21 at halftime and increased its advantage to 57-33 on Morrison?s three-point play with 10:36 left. Centenary cut its deficit to 68-58 on Aaron Harwell?s basket with 2:44 remaining, but Morrison responded with a three-point play to ignite a clinching 8-0 run. Bell-Holter had a game-high eight rebounds as Oral Roberts outrebounded Centenary 43-28. The Golden Eagles have 14 consecutive wins over the Gents.
